### Hadith 2:25

*Narrated Aisha:*

(the wife of the Prophet) The people used to come from their abodes and
from Al-'Awali (i.e. outskirts of Medina up to a distance of four miles
or more from Medina). They used to pass through dust and used to be
drenched with sweat and covered with dust; so sweat used to trickle from
them. One of them came to Allah's Apostle who was in my house. The
Prophet said to him, "I wish that you keep yourself clean on this day of
yours (i.e. take a bath)."

